b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Lewis vs. Abdurakhimov</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 102</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on December 9, 2016, at <a href="/wiki/Times_Union_Center" title="Times Union Center">Times Union Center</a> in <a href="/wiki/Albany,_New_York" title="Albany, New York">Albany</a>, <a href="/wiki/New_York_(state)" title="New York (state)">New York</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-UFN102_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-UFN102-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>This event was the first that the organization hosted in Albany.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-UFN102_2-1"><a href="#cite_note-UFN102-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A heavyweight bout between <a href="/wiki/Derrick_Lewis_(fighter)" title="Derrick Lewis (fighter)">Derrick Lewis</a> and <a href="/wiki/Shamil_Abdurakhimov" title="Shamil Abdurakhimov">Shamil Abdurakhimov</a> served as the event headliner.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-headliner_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-headliner-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A middleweight bout between <a href="/wiki/Josh_Samman" title="Josh Samman">Josh Samman</a> and <a href="/wiki/Oluwale_Bamgbose" title="Oluwale Bamgbose">Oluwale Bamgbose</a> was briefly linked to the event. However the pairing never materialized as Samman died on October 5, 2016.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup> Joe Gigliotti was tabbed as his replacement.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-headliner_3-1"><a href="#cite_note-headliner-3">[3]</a></sup> In turn, Bamgbose pulled out of the fight in mid-November citing an injury and was replaced by promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Gerald_Meerschaert" title="Gerald Meerschaert">Gerald Meerschaert</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>Promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Charlie_Ward_(fighter)" title="Charlie Ward (fighter)">Charlie Ward</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Randy_Brown_(fighter)" title="Randy Brown (fighter)">Randy Brown</a> at the event. However, Ward was pulled from the event in early November due to alleged <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Visa_(document)" title="Visa (document)">visa</a> issues which restricted his travel and was replaced by fellow newcomer <a href="/wiki/Brian_Camozzi" title="Brian Camozzi">Brian Camozzi</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Brown/Camozzi_6-0"><a href="#cite_note-Brown/Camozzi-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Zubaira_Tukhugov" title="Zubaira Tukhugov">Zubaira Tukhugov</a> was scheduled to face Tiago Trator at the event. However, on November 14, Tukhugov was pulled from the card after being notified by <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/USADA" title="USADA">USADA</a> of a potential anti-doping violation stemming from an out-of-competition sample collected earlier.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup> On November 28, Tukhugov was replaced by promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Shane_Burgos" title="Shane Burgos">Shane Burgos</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Aljamain_Sterling" title="Aljamain Sterling">Aljamain Sterling</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Raphael_Assun%C3%A7%C3%A3o" title="Raphael Assun\xc3\xa7\xc3\xa3o">Raphael Assun\xc3\xa7\xc3\xa3o</a> at the event. However, Sterling pulled out of the fight on November 23 citing injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup> Assun\xc3\xa7\xc3\xa3o was subsequently removed from the card with the pairing expected to be rescheduled for a future event.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-11"><a href="#cite_note-11">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/The_Ultimate_Fighter:_Team_Joanna_vs._Team_Cl%C3%A1udia" title="The Ultimate Fighter: Team Joanna vs. Team Cl\xc3\xa1udia">The Ultimate Fighter: Team Joanna vs. Team Cl\xc3\xa1udia</a> women\'s strawweight winner <a href="/wiki/Tatiana_Suarez" title="Tatiana Suarez">Tatiana Suarez</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Juliana_Lima" title="Juliana Lima">Juliana Lima</a> at the event. However, Suarez pulled out of the fight on November 23 citing injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-12"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup> She was replaced on December 2 by promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/JJ_Aldrich" title="JJ Aldrich">JJ Aldrich</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-shortnotice_13-0"><a href="#cite_note-shortnotice-13">[13]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Patrick_Cummins_(fighter)" title="Patrick Cummins (fighter)">Patrick Cummins</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Gian_Villante" title="Gian Villante">Gian Villante</a> at the event. However, Cummins pulled out of the fight on December 2 citing a <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Staph_infection" title="Staph infection">staph infection</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-14"><a href="#cite_note-14">[14]</a></sup> He was replaced by promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Saparbek_Safarov" title="Saparbek Safarov">Saparbek Safarov</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-15"><a href="#cite_note-15">[15]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>At the weigh-ins, <a href="/wiki/Justine_Kish" title="Justine Kish">Justine Kish</a> came in at 116.4 lbs, over the women\'s strawweight limit of 116 lbs. As a result, Kish was fined 20% of her purse, which will go to her opponent <a href="/wiki/Ashley_Yoder" title="Ashley Yoder">Ashley Yoder</a> and the bout proceeded as scheduled at a catchweight.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-weight_16-0"><a href="#cite_note-weight-16">[16]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-17"><a href="#cite_note-17">[17]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses:<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-18"><a href="#cite_note-18">[18]</a></sup>\n</p>]'